  <div id="sectionCarryOver">
  <h2>The Discipline is:</h2>
  <p>an <span class="def" id="out-of-school-suspension">out-of-school suspension*</span>  that exceeds a total of 10 <span class="def" id="school-days">school days*</span> when combined  with other out-of-school suspensions this school year.</p>
</div>
  <h2>Response:</h2>
  <p>Is the  removal for more than 10 consecutive schools days?  If yes, this is a  disciplinary <span class="def" id="change-of-placement">change of placement*</span>.<sup class="statute">1</sup>  Because the removal is considered to be a  change of placement, a <span class="def" id="manifestation-determination">manifestation determination*</span> meeting must be  held. </p>
  <p><a href="/school-discipline-information/504/37-greater-than-10-pattern.asp">This is a disciplinary change of placement  - Continue Here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a></p>
  <p>  	If  the sum of all  suspensions for this  school year total 10 or more nonconsecutive school days, the school must  determine whether this suspension is this part of a series of suspensions that  constitutes a <span class="def" id="pattern-of-removals">pattern of removals*</span> <sup class="statute">2</sup> because:</p>
	<ul>
		<li>the series of suspensions totals more  than 10 consecutive school days, and</li>
		<li>the behavior is substantially similar  to previous incidents and</li>
		<li>because of  other factors such as the length of suspensions, the total amount of time suspended  and the proximity of the suspensions to one another constitutes a pattern.</li>
	</ul>
	<p>The  school district determines on a case-by-case basis whether a pattern of suspensions constitutes a change of placement.<sup class="statute">3</sup> <br />
		If  the school district determines that the pattern of suspensions constitutes  a change of placement, a manifestation determination meeting  must be held. </p>
  <p><a href="/school-discipline-information/504/37-greater-than-10-pattern.asp">The school district determined this constitutes a  change of placement - Continue Here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a></p>
	<p>		If  multiple suspensions were for a total of 10 or more school days, but the school  determines that the suspensions do not constitute a change of placement, no  manifestation determination meeting is required. </p>
  <p><a href="/school-discipline-information/73-conclusion.asp">The school district determined this does not constitute a change of placement - Continue Here &gt;&gt;&gt;</a>  </p>
